//  Redux part

-> ** Redux:- It is a state management JS library. It simply helps to manage the state of our application.
-> It provides a predictable state container by connecting components to a centralized store, and enabling efficient management of application state across components.
-> There is a single store where we put our global state, and that state data is available to the entire application
-> In one application, there is only 1 store.

-> Advantages
    Centralized state management system (Store)
    Performance Optimizations
    Pure reducer function

-> principles of Redux
    single source of truth
    state is read-only
    Changes are made with pure functions

-> work of Redux
-> Store : Centralized state management system (only one store in a application)
-> Reducer : Pure function which have state and action (multiple reducer) changes the state
-> Action : It is an object where we have type and payload
{type:'' , payload:''}
-> Action Creators: are functions that take a few inputs as function arguments and return an action with type and payload
-> Dispatch: a store in Redux has a method on it called dispatch, which is called with an action object when we wish to update the current state (triggering an event )
-> Selectors  :  these are just plain functions that receive the state as an argument and extract specific pieces of information from the current state

-> How we use or implement redux
-> Old Way
redux with react redux
-> New way
redux toolkit with react redux

-> Redux Toolkit (RTK)
It is used for writing redux code but in more concise way.RTK abstracts the basic redux code and provides us boilerplates that enables us to write redux code in less lines of code.
https://redux-toolkit.js.org/
npm install @reduxjs/toolkit react-redux --save
-> @reduxjs/toolkit
-> configureStore() function : to create a store
-> createSlice() : create action and reducer in a single function

> react-redux
-> Provider : It provide store to the application
-> useSelector : get state data from redux
-> useDispatch : dispatch actions to the reducer to update state data


